cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image denoising using neural networks. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories as it proposes a new neural network architecture and activation function. Additionally, it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves developing a model that can learn to denoise images. Finally, it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with image processing.
